### Knowledge Base Management - Smoke Tests
### Tester les endpoints CRUD de la base de patterns

# Variables
@host = http://localhost:8000
@newPatternId = custom_test_pattern_001

### 1. GET /rag/stats - Vérifier la base
GET {{host}}/rag/stats

### 2. GET /rag/patterns - Lister tous les patterns
GET {{host}}/rag/patterns

### 3. GET /rag/patterns/{id} - Obtenir un pattern spécifique
GET {{host}}/rag/patterns/py_001

### 4. POST /rag/patterns - Créer un nouveau pattern
POST {{host}}/rag/patterns
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "{{newPatternId}}",
  "language": "python",
  "pattern": "Always use context managers for file operations",
  "category": "style",
  "severity": "high",
  "rule": "FILE_CONTEXT_MANAGER_CUSTOM",
  "bad_example": "f = open('file.txt')\ndata = f.read()\nf.close()",
  "good_example": "with open('file.txt') as f:\n    data = f.read()"
}

### 5. GET /rag/patterns/{id} - Vérifier le pattern créé
GET {{host}}/rag/patterns/{{newPatternId}}

### 6. PUT /rag/patterns/{id} - Mettre à jour le pattern
PUT {{host}}/rag/patterns/{{newPatternId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "severity": "critical",
  "rule": "FILE_CONTEXT_MANAGER_CRITICAL"
}

### 7. POST /rag/retrieve - Rechercher patterns pertinents
POST {{host}}/rag/retrieve
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "f = open('test.txt')\ndata = f.read()\nf.close()",
  "language": "python",
  "category": "style"
}

### 8. DELETE /rag/patterns/{id} - Supprimer le pattern test
DELETE {{host}}/rag/patterns/{{newPatternId}}

### 9. GET /rag/patterns/{id} - Vérifier la suppression (doit retourner 404)
GET {{host}}/rag/patterns/{{newPatternId}}

### 10. GET /rag/stats - Vérifier le nombre final de patterns
GET {{host}}/rag/stats
